WorkItem.Description:
I have found this issue using a LinLog Layout.  Other layouts may or may not be affected.

Assume you start with a single node.  The node has one button to show child nodes.

If I click the button, all the children are placed directly over the first node.

To correct this, I modified InitializePosition in GraphLayout.GraphElements.cs

original: 
protected virtual void InitializePosition(TVertex vertex)
{
...
 if (count > 0)
 {
  pos.X /= count;
  pos.Y /= count;
 ...
 }
}

to the following

protected virtual void InitializePosition(TVertex vertex)
{
...
 if (count > 0)
 {
  if (count == 1)
   count++;
  pos.X /= count;
  pos.Y /= count;
 ...
 }
}
